# Rename the text
nyt.df <- corpus$documents
for (i in 1:dim(nyt.df)[1]) {
  filename <- paste0("texts/", 1000+i, nyt.df$author[i], "-", nyt.df$date[i], ".txt")
  sink(file = filename) %>% # open file to write 
  cat(nyt.df[i,"texts"])  # write the file
  sink()
  print(i)
}

# Get Corpus
nyt_corpus <- VCorpus(DirSource("texts/"))

# Clean Corpus 
removeNumPunct <- function(x){gsub("[^[:alpha:][:space:]]*", "", x)}
clean_corpus <- function(corpus){
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, content_transformer(tolower))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, content_transformer(replace_symbol))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeWords, c(stopwords("en")))  
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, stripWhitespace)
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeNumbers)
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, content_transformer(removeNumPunct))
  return(corpus)
}
nyt_clean <- clean_corpus(nyt_corpus)

nyt_stemmed <- tm_map(nyt_clean, stemDocument) # Stem the words

nyt_tdm <- TermDocumentMatrix(nyt_stemmed) # Transform to a Term Document Matrix 

nyt_td <- tidy(nyt_tdm)
nyt_td$document <- substr(nyt_td$document, 5, nchar(nyt_td$document) - 4)
nyt_td$date <- substr(nyt_td$document, nchar(nyt_td$document) - 9, nchar(nyt_td$document))
nyt_td$author <- substr(nyt_td$document, 1, nchar(nyt_td$document) - 11)
nyt_td %>% group_by(term) %>% summarise(n = sum(count)) %>% top_n(n = 20, wt = n) %>% mutate(term = reorder(term, n)) %>% ggplot(aes(term, n)) + geom_bar(stat = "identity", color = "white", fill = "skyblue") + xlab(NULL)  + ylab("Count") + coord_flip() + theme_tufte() + ggtitle("20 Most Frequent Words") + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

sentiment analysis Tone

pos <- read.table("C:/Users/1/Desktop/Columbia/CU/Spring 2017/Data Visualization/QMSS-G4063-Data-Visualization/Assignments/Assignment 3/dictionaries/positive-words.txt", as.is=T)
neg <- read.table("C:/Users/1/Desktop/Columbia/CU/Spring 2017/Data Visualization/QMSS-G4063-Data-Visualization/Assignments/Assignment 3/dictionaries/negative-words.txt", as.is=T)

sentiment <- function(words){ 
  n = length(words)
  out = rep(NA_real_, n)
  for (i in 1:n){
    tok <- quanteda::tokenize(words[i]) 
    pos.count <- sum(tok[[1]]%in%pos[,1]) 
    neg.count <- sum(tok[[1]]%in%neg[,1]) 
    out[i] <- (pos.count - neg.count)/(pos.count+neg.count) 
  }
  return(out)
}

df <- corpus$documents
df$sentiment <- sentiment(corpus$documents$texts)

# data restructure 
df$candidate[df$trump_article == TRUE & df$clinton_article == FALSE] <- "Trump only"
df$candidate[df$trump_article == FALSE & df$clinton_article == TRUE] <- "Clinton only"
df$candidate[df$trump_article == TRUE & df$clinton_article == TRUE] <- "Both"
df$candidate[df$trump_article == FALSE & df$clinton_article == FALSE] <- "None"
#Figure 8
df %>% filter(candidate != "None") %>% ggplot(aes(x = author, y = sentiment)) + geom_boxplot(aes(color = author)) + theme_tufte() + facet_wrap(~candidate) + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) + ggtitle("Sentiment about Candidates") + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), legend.position = "None", strip.background = element_rect(colour = "grey", fill = "grey"))
nyt_td$document <- substr(nyt_td$document, 5, nchar(nyt_td$document) - 4)
df$month <- substr(df$date, 1, nchar(df$date) - 3)
# compute the average sentiment over each month
change <- df %>% filter(candidate == "Trump only" | candidate == "Clinton only") %>% group_by(candidate, month) %>% summarise(ave_sentiment = mean(sentiment))
# Figure 9 Effects of Political Events
change %>% ggplot(aes(x = month, y = ave_sentiment)) + geom_line(aes(group = candidate, color = candidate)) + geom_point(aes(shape = candidate, color = candidate), size = 2) + scale_colour_manual(values = c("navy", "red3")) + theme_tufte() + ggtitle("Average Sentiment Change \n Trump vs Clinton") + theme(legend.position = "top") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = -45, hjust = 0)) + xlab("Date") + ylab("Agerage Sentiment") + theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 18, hjust = 0.45)) + geom_vline(xintercept = c(7.75, 11.27, 13.6), lty=2, color ="grey") + annotate("text", x = c(10.58, 12.68, 14.78), y = 0.09,
